{{rfc}}
A slang term used as a riposte and often as a counter-riposte to an insulting statement (and recently, even to non-insulting statements). An alternative form is "yo momma."

Some examples:
''"You're an idiot."''
''"Your mom is an idiot!"''

Sometimes it is used as a clever way to skew another person's words or as a non-sequitur:

''"Ramen noodles are cheap and easy."''
''"Your mom is cheap and easy!"''

This use of "your mom" is different from [[the dozens]] in that no response is expected from the first person, as the "your mom" builds off of the original sentence. It is not a contest but a one-time retort.

''"Samuel is an idiot."''
''"Samuel's mom is an idiot!"''

"Your mom" ripostes are so common that the entire phrase is sometimes no longer necessary.

''"You're an idiot.""
''"Yo momma!"''

